I do see your point. I did use it here though because of "glance_internal_endpoint". It is used in the following files:

```
rafael@rafael-Inspiron-5437:~/git/kolla-ansible$ grep  -R "glance_internal_endpoint" .
./ansible/roles/cinder/templates/cinder.conf.j2:glance_api_servers = {{ glance_internal_endpoint }}
./ansible/roles/nova-hyperv/templates/nova_hyperv.conf.j2:api_servers = {{ glance_internal_endpoint }}
./ansible/roles/ironic/templates/ironic.conf.j2:glance_api_servers = {{ glance_internal_endpoint }}
./ansible/roles/glance/tasks/register.yml:    - {'interface': 'internal', 'url': '{{ glance_internal_endpoint }}'}
./ansible/roles/nova/templates/nova.conf.j2:api_servers = {{glance_internal_endpoint }}
./ansible/group_vars/all.yml:glance_internal_endpoint: "{{ internal_protocol }}://{{ glance_internal_fqdn }}:{{ glance_api_port }}"
